tos%2C%20birth%20details%2C%20and%20ethnicities%20of%20potentially%20millions%20of%2023andMe%20customers%20are%20peddling%20the%20information%20on%20the%20dark%20web%20for%20thousands%20of%20dollars.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20gathered%20from%20user%20credentials%20that%20were%20exposed%20in%20prior%20data%20breaches%2C%20and%20the%20company's%20security%20systems%20have%20not%20been%20breached%2C%20according%20to%2023andMe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20preliminary%20results%20of%20this%20investigation%20suggest%20that%20the%20login%20credentials%20used%20in%20these%20access%20attempts%20may%20have%20been%20gathered%20by%20a%20threat%20actor%20from%20data%20leaked%20during%20incidents%20involving%20other%20online%20platforms%20where%20users%20have%20recycled%20login%20credentials%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20company%20told%20Insider.%20%C2%A0In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20hackers%20plugged%20in%20leaked%20username-password%20combinations%20into%2023andMe%20accounts%20in%20a%20technique%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bcredential%20stuffing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20first%20became%20aware%20of%20the%20attack%20in%20a%20post%20on%20Reddit%20that%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20removed%20by%20the%20platform.%20Since%20then%2C%20hackers%20have%20taken%20to%20hawking%20the%20data%20on%20the%20cybercrime%20marketplace%2C%20BreachForums.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20anonymous%20seller%20advertised%20the%20data%20on%20BreachForums%20earlier%20this%20week%20as%20containing%20%26quot%3BDNA%20profiles%20of%20millions%2C%20ranging%20from%20the%20world's%20top%20business%20magnates%20to%20dynasties%20often%20whispered%20about%20in%20conspiracy%20theories%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20noted%20that%20each%20set%20of%20data%20also%20came%20with%20%26quot%3Bcorresponding%20email%20addresses%2C%26quot%3B%20based%20on%20a%20repost%20of%20the%20ad%20on%20X.%20The%20sample%20data%20reportedly%20contains%20entries%20for%20tech%20execs%20like%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%2C%20Sergey%20Brin%2C%20and%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2F23andme-credential-stuffing-data-stolen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Wired%2C%20but%20its%20unclear%20whether%20the%20entries%20are%20legitimate.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F23andme-ceo-anne-wojcicki-life-career-family-photos-2021-3%5C%22%3Ecompany%20is%20helmed%20by%20Anne%20Wojcicki%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20sister%20of%20former%20YouTube%20CEO%20Susan%20Wojcicki%20and%20ex-wife%20of%20Sergey%20Brin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20seller%20offered%20profile%20bundles%20starting%20at%20%241000%20for%20100%20profiles%20going%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%20%24100%2C000%20for%20100%2C000%20profiles%2C%20noting%20that%20for%20each%20bulk%20purchase%20of%2010%2C000%20they'd%20offer%20the%20flexibility%20of%20incremental%20payments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20post%20on%20BreachForums%2C%20also%20reposted%20to%20X%2C%20noted%20that%20the%20data%20contained%20%26quot%3Bhalf%20of%20the%20members%20of%2023andMe.%26quot%3B%20The%20company%2C%20which%20has%20a%20total%2014%20million%20users%2C%20has%20yet%20to%20confirm%20the%20number%20of%20compromised%20user%20accounts%20and%20also%20noted%20that%20no%20raw%20genetic%20data%20was%20shared.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBased%20on%20the%20results%20of%20its%20preliminary%20investigation%2C%20the%20company%20believes%20the%20hackers%20gained%20access%20to%20a%20much%20smaller%20number%20of%20user%20accounts%2C%20but%20managed%20to%20scrape%20the%20data%20of%20several%20other%2023andMe%20users%20through%20a%20feature%20called%20DNA%20Relatives.%20The%20feature%20allows%20users%20to%20connect%20with%20and%20see%20information%20about%20other%20users%20they%20shared%20a%20%26quot%3Brecent%20ancestor%26quot%3B%20with%20%E2%80%94%20which%20they%20define%20as%20less%20than%20nine%20generations%20back%20on%20their%20website.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E23andMe%20also%20did%20not%20confirm%20whether%20the%20attack%20was%20directed%20toward%20any%20particular%20ethnic%20group.%20A%20post%20on%20BreachForums%20from%20earlier%20this%20week%20touted%20the%20data%20sample%20as%20%26quot%3B1%20million%20Ashkenazi%20database%26quot%3B%20though%20an%20individual%20could%20be%20classified%20as%20Ashkenazi%20Jew%20even%20with%20just%201%25%20Jewish%20ancestry%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company.%20Those%20with%20European%20or%20Ashkenazi%20ancestry%20are%20likely%20to%20have%20many%20matches%20via%20the%20DNA%20Relatives%20feature%20compared%20to%20people%20with%20Asian%20or%20Middle%20Eastern%20ancestry%2C%2023andMe%20also%20notes%20on%20its%20website.%20There%20may%20also%20be%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20users%20of%20Chinese%20descent%26quot%3B%20impacted%20by%20the%20leak%2C%26quot%3B%20Wired%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2F23andme-credential-stuffing-data-stolen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E23andMe%2C%20which%20was%20founded%20in%202006%2C%20made%20waves%20for%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-tried-the-new-23andme-genetic-test-2015-12%23after-seven-weeks-my-results-arrived-via-email-in-total-i-had-62-reports-waiting-for-me-based-on-my-23-pairs-of-chromosomes-from-mom-and-dad-the-reports-covered-everything-from-family-history-to-physical-traits-and-genetic-variants-related-to-diseases-that-i-could-pass-down-to-my-kids-7%5C%22%3Esaliva%20tests%20which%20could%20test%20for%20genetic%20predispositions%2C%20ancestry%2C%20and%20inherited%20traits%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20company%20%E2%80%94%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-delete-dna-genetic-data-2018-5%5C%22%3Eshares%20anonymized%20user%20data%20with%20their%20consent%20with%20third%20parties%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20is%20encouraging%20users