0as%20calculating%20as%20it%20is%20ruthless.%20That's%20what%20kept%20it%20in%20control%20of%20Gaza%20since%202007%20despite%20being%20under%20constant%20threat%20from%20Israel%2C%20as%20well%20as%20from%20still%20more%20radical%20Salafist%20and%20other%20Islamist%20groups%20within%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnly%20Hamas%20knows%20the%20details%20of%20its%20strategy%20for%20Saturday's%20attack%2C%20but%20the%20potential%20fallout%20is%20plain%20to%20see.%20A%20war%20in%20Gaza%20threatens%20at%20a%20stroke%20to%20upend%20the%20direction%20of%20travel%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20It%20puts%20Israel%20in%20the%20invidious%20position%20of%20having%20to%20choose%20between%20appearing%20weak%20-%20a%20dangerous%20strategy%20in%20the%20region%20-%20and%20inflicting%20the%20kind%20of%20mass%20casualties%20in%20the%20crowded%20Gaza%20Strip%20that%20will%20enrage%20Israel's%20entire%20Palestinian%20population%2C%20forcing%20tough%20decisions%20on%20Arab%20leaders%20in%20the%20Gulf%20and%20beyond.%20Already%20on%20Saturday%20there%20were%20reports%20of%20160%20Palestinian%20dead%20and%20more%20than%201000%20wounded%20in%20Israel's%20retaliatory%20airstrikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20has%20had%20success%20normalizing%20relations%20with%20parts%20of%20the%20Arab%20world%20while%20supporting%20the%20expansion%20of%20Jewish%20settlements%20on%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%2C%20at%20best%2C%20slow%20walking%20prospects%20for%20Palestinian%20statehood.%20Since%202020%2C%20Israel%20has%20signed%20US-brokered%20recognition%20agreements%20with%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20Bahrain%2C%20Morocco%20and%20Sudan.%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20home%20to%20Mecca%2C%20has%20been%20considering%20a%20deal.%20Even%20Turkey's%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdogan%2C%20who%20for%20years%20had%20positioned%20himself%20as%20champion%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%20for%20domestic%20political%20gain%2C%20met%20with%20Israel's%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20for%20the%20first%20time%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESaturday's%20calls%20from%20Erdogan%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Egypt%20and%20others%20for%20de-escalation%20came%20quickly%20and%20were%20doubtless%20genuine.%20All%20of%20them%20know%20the%20political%20pressures%20they%20will%20come%20under%20to%20condemn%20and%20break%20ties%20with%20Israel%20if%20Palestinian%20casualties%20mount.%20That%20now%20seems%20inevitable.%20Netanyahu%20said%20his%20country%20was%20at%20war%2C%20while%20Major%20General%20Ghasan%20Alyan%20said%20Hamas%20had%20%26quot%3Bopened%20the%20gates%20of%20hell%20to%20the%20Gaza%20strip%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20clip%20to%20camera%20posted%20on%20the%20Israeli%20Defense%20Forces'%20feed%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlyan%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20Hamas%20will%20bear%20responsibility%20for%20the%20consequences%2C%20but%20no%20matter%20how%20true%20that%20may%20be%20-%20and%20it%20is%20-%20the%20question%20of%20who%20fired%20first%20on%20Saturday%20will%20count%20for%20little%20in%20the%20Muslim%20world.%20There%2C%20popular%20outrage%20over%20Israeli%20actions%20in%20recent%20months%20and%20years%2C%20in%20particular%20around%20the%20Al-Aqsa%20mosque%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20had%20been%20mounting.%20Alyan's%20words%20will%20resonate%20less%20than%20those%20of%20Mohammed%20Deif%2C%20a%20Hamas%20military%20commander%2C%20who%20said%20that%20%26quot%3BOperation%20Al-Aqsa%20Flood%26quot%3B%20was%20launched%20because%20%26quot%3Benough%20is%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlready%2C%20the%20Saudi%20government%20statement%20calling%20for%20calm%20on%20Saturday%20sought%20to%20position%20Hamas's%20actions%20as%20retaliatory%2C%20recalling%20the%20kingdom's%20%26quot%3Brepeated%20warnings%20of%20the%20dangers%20of%20the%20explosion%20of%20the%20situation%2C%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20continued%20occupation%2C%20the%20deprivation%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20of%20their%20legitimate%20rights%2C%20and%20the%20repetition%20of%20systematic%20provocations