Said%20on%20the%20Suez%20Canal%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651e2b2442ecf94db4786d65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPort%20Said%20on%20the%20Suez%20Canal%20in%201880.%3Cp%3EBildagentur-Online%2FUig%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBly%20arrived%20at%20Port%20Said%2C%20Egypt%2C%20on%20November%2027%2C%201889%20and%20traveled%20southward%20toward%20Yemen.%20In%20early%20January%201890%2C%20Bisland%20sailed%20the%20opposite%20way%20through%20the%20canal%2C%20entering%20near%20Yemen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20women%20had%20plenty%20of%20time%20to%20take%20in%20the%20buildings%2C%20encampments%2C%20and%20camels.%20Ships%20in%20the%20Suez%20Canal%20traveled%20slow%20enough%20that%20Bly%20could%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigital.library.upenn.edu%2Fwomen%2Fbly%2Fworld%2Fworld.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexchange%20pleasantries%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20passengers%20on%20other%20vessels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20ships%20went%20through%20faster%20than%20that%2C%20the%20waves%20would%20stir%20up%20the%20dirt%20and%20erode%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20canal%2C%26quot%3B%20Goodman%20said.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fever-given-logged-speed-limit-before-running-aground-suez-2021-3%5C%22%3Ecanal's%20speed%20limit%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20still%20between%207.6%20knots%20and%208.6%20knots%2C%20just%20under%2010%20miles%20per%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20as%20in%20other%20countries%20the%20two%20women%20visited%2C%20accounts%20of%20their%20journeys%20include%20stereotypical%20and%20offensive%20descriptions%20of%20the%20native%20people%20they%20saw%20and%20interacted%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20sun%20never%20set%20on%20the%20British%20Empire%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20commonwealths%2C%20countries%2C%20and%20colonies%20on%20six%20continents%2C%20Britain's%20reach%20was%20inescapable%20during%20Bly's%20and%20Bisland's%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20traveling%20through%20the%20length%20and%20breadth%20of%20the%20British%20Empire%2C%26quot%3B%20Goodman%20said%2C%20stopping%20in%20its%20ports%20all%20along%20the%20way.%20Aden%2C%20Colombo%2C%20Penang%2C%20and%20Hong%20Kong%20were%20all%20under%20British%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20I%20traveled%20on%20and%20realized%20more%20than%20ever%20before%20how%20the%20English%20have%20stolen%20almost%20all%2C%20if%20not%20all%2C%20desirable%20sea%20ports%2C%26quot%3B%20Bly%20wrote%2C%20she%20no%20longer%20marveled%20at%20%26quot%3Bthe%20pride%20with%20which%20Englishmen%20view%20their%20flag%20floating%20in%20so%20many%20different%20climes%20and%20over%20so%20many%20different%20nationalities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20colored%20lithograph%20of%20people%20onshore%20supervisors%20workers%20laying%20a%20telegraph%20cable%20near%20a%20boat%20at%20the%20port%20of%20Aden%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651e2fbf2ce014759e755826%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWorkers%20lay%20a%20telegraph%20cable%20at%20the%20port%20of%20Aden%20in%20what%20is%20now%20Yemen%20circa%201870.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBisland%2C%20too%2C%20noted%20war%20ships%20guarded%20Aden%2C%20which%20was%20%26quot%3Bvaluable%3B%20and%20therefore%2C%20like%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20Singapore%2C%20Penang%2C%20Ceylon%20%E2%80%94%20like%20everything%20much%20worth%20having%20in%20this%20part%20of%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20it%20is%20an%20English%20possession.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBritish%20citizens%20could%20travel%20halfway%20around%20the%20world%20and%20still%20speak%20English%2C%20eat%20British%20food%2C%20read%20London%20newspapers%2C%20and%20stay%20in%20European%20hotels%2C%20Goodman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%