s%20before%20antibiotics.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20penicillin%2C%26quot%3B%20Behn%20said.%20%26quot%3BHopefully%20some%20of%20those%20doctor%20surgeons%20are%20nearby%20in%20case%20anything%20goes%20wrong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELuxury%20liners%20and%20lung%20disease%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBly%20and%20Bisland%20voyaged%20via%20first-class%20accommodations%20whenever%20possible.%20Nowhere%20was%20the%20difference%20more%20stark%20than%20the%20steamships%2C%20where%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigitalcollections.nypl.org%2Fitems%2F510d47db-43a6-a3d9-e040-e00a18064a99%23%2F%3Fuuid%3D510d47db-43a4-a3d9-e040-e00a18064a99%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esingle%20meal%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20include%20soup%2C%20fish%2C%20beef%2C%20duck%2C%20potatoes%2C%20salad%2C%20pastry%2C%20cheese%2C%20and%20fruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%20the%20more%20sumptuous%20accommodations%2C%20hundreds%20of%20steerage%20passengers%20were%20crammed%20in%20airless%20rooms%20with%20unwashed%20dishes%20and%20clothes%2C%20and%20pools%20of%20vomit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst-class%20rooms%20were%20further%20from%20the%20ceaseless%20vibration%20of%20the%20engines%20that%20stokers%2C%20or%20coal%20shovelers%2C%20worked%20furiously%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20see%20a%20huge%20emphasis%20being%20placed%20on%20building%20ships%20that%20were%20ever%20faster%20than%20the%20previous%20generation%20of%20ships%2C%26quot%3B%20Goodman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20passengers%20enjoyed%20the%20idea%20of%20being%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bfastest%26quot%3B%20ship.%20And%20Bly%20had%20a%20race%20to%20win.%20She'd%20only%20recently%20learned%20that%20she%20wasn't%20just%20competing%20against%20time.%20A%20steamship%20company%20employee%20had%20shocked%20her%20with%20the%20news%20that%20Bisland%20was%20in%20the%20race%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20journey%20between%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20San%20Francisco%20in%20late%20December%2C%20Bly%20urged%20the%20ship%20captain%20to%20go%20faster.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20fail%2C%20I%20will%20never%20return%20to%20New%20York%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Several%20shirtless%20men%20shovel%20coal%20from%20a%20large%20pile%20on%20a%20ship%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651e4364617692f0d03fa8c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoal%20stokers%20shovel%20coal%20on%20a%20ship%20circa%201920s.%3Cp%3ESSPL%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20way%20that%20that%20could%20happen%20is%20because%20you%20had%20these%20men%20down%20in%20the%20bowels%20of%20the%20ship%20shoveling%20coal%20in%20the%20most%20abject%20working%20conditions%20imaginable%2C%26quot%3B%20Goodman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stokers%20shoveled%20up%202%20tons%20of%20coal%20a%20day%20in%20rooms%20that%20could%20reach%20130%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20Goodman%20said.%20Their%20shovels%20could%20get%20hot%20enough%20to%20blister%20their%20hands.%20Inhaling%20coal%20dust%20led%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lung.org%2Flung-health-diseases%2Flung-disease-lookup%2Fblack-lung%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epneumoconiosis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20known%20as%20black%20lung%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20doctor%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FThe_Occupational_Diseases%2FZbq3SU981igC%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3D%2522dyspneic%2Band%2Bshort%2Blived%2522%26pg%3DPA417%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edescribed%3C%2Fa%3E%20coal%20miners'%20and%20stokers'%20lungs%20during%20autopsies.%20They%20were%20leathery%20and%20coated%20in%20thick%20black%20mucus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETelegrams%20and%20travel%20delays%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EQueen%20Victoria%20sent%20President%20James%20Buchanan%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fatlantic-cable.com%2FArticle%2F1858Messages%2Findex.htm%5C%22%3Etelegram%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20August%2016%2C%201858.%20It%20celebrated%20the%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffiberoptic-internet-cables-ocean-bottom-map-2015-9%5C%22%3Etransatlantic%20cable%3C%2Fa%3E%20joining%20Europe%20and%20North%20America.%20People%20could%20send%20messages%20between%20the%20continents%20more%20quickly%20than%20ever%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20kinks%20in%20the%20system.%20New%20advances%20in%20the%201870s%20meant%20the%20cables%20could%20finally%20transmit%20more%20than%20one%20message%20at%20a%20time.%20Adding%20more%20cables%20helped%20lower%20the%20price%20of%20sending%20a%20telegram%2C%20too%2C%20to%20about%2031%20cents%20in%20the%20US.%20By%201889%2C%20a%20message%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fwall-street-1889-the-telegraph-ramps-up-trading-speed-1404765917%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20transatlantic%20cables%20in%20about%20five%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencemuseum.org.uk%2Fobjects-and-stories%2Fhow-perseverance-laid-first-transatlantic-telegraph-cable%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewasn't%20until%3C%2Fa%3E%201902%20that%20cables%20stretched%20all%20the%20way%20around%20the%20world.%20Still%2C%20Bly%20and%20Bisland%20managed%20to%20dash%20off%20quick%20notes%20to%20their%20editors%20from%20various%20ports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20cables%20were%20actually%20few%20and%20far%20between%2C%26quot%3B%20Behn%20said%2C%20much%20to%20Joseph%20Pulitzer's%20chagrin.%20The%20owner%20of%20The%20World%2C%20the%20paper%20Bly%20worked%20for%2C%20hoped%20to%20entice%20readers%20to%20follow%20her%20adventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20editors%20cooked%20up%20a%20contest.%20The%20person%20who%20came%20closest%20to%20guessing%20Bly's%20return%20time%20would%20win%20a%20trip%20to%20Europe.%20Naturally%2C%20entrants%20had%20to%20fill%20out%20a%20slip%20available%20in%20each%20Sunday's%20edition%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bthe%20more%20expensive%20paper%2C%26quot%3B%20Behn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Bly%20arrived%20in%20San%20Francisco%20on%20January%2021%2C%201890%2C%20she%20had%20another%20unwelcome%20surprise.%20A%20massive%20snowstorm%20had%20delayed%20the%20train%20she%20was%20supposed%20to%20take%20back%20east.%20Instead%2C%20her%20editors%20spent%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20to%20get%20Bly%20her%20own%20private%20train%20that%20would%20take%20a%20route%20avoiding%20the%20bad%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20aboard%20the%20train%2C%20Bly%20began%20to%20receive%20telegrams%20from%20her%20editors%20and%20well-wishers.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20it%20literally%20literally%20just%20says%2C%20'Nelly%20Bly's%20train%2C'%26quot%3B%20Behn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJules%20Verne%2C%20whom%20Bly%20met%20in%20France%20during%20her%20trek%2C%20sent%20her%20a%20congratulatory%20telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20of%20several%20women%20working%20at%20telegraph%20machines%20at%20the%20Post%20Office%20Telegraph%20Headquarters%20in%20London%20in%201871%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651e479842ecf94db478731d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWomen%20working%20in%20the%20main%20instrument%20room%20at%20London's%20Post%20Office%20Telegraph%20Headquarters%20in%201871.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20a%20few%20times%20when%20communications%20technology%20more%20reliable%20and%20accessible%20than%20the%20telegraph%20would%20have%20helped%20the%20travelers.%20A%20man%20who%20said%20he%20was%20from%20the%20Thomas%20Cook%20%26amp%3B%20Son%20travel%20agency%20approached%20Bisland%20as%20she%20disembarked%20from%20a%20train%20in%20Italy%20on%20January%2016%2C%201890.%20The%20boat%20she'd%20been%20hoping%20would%20wait%20for%20her%20had%20sailed%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20like%20she%20can%20send%20her%20boss%20a%20quick%20email%2C%26quot%3B%20Behn%20said.%20Instead%20of%20sailing%20home%20from%20France%2C%20Bisland%20had%20to%20make%20her%20way%20to%20London%20then%20Ireland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20the%20man%20had%20been%20wrong.%20The%20ship%20was%20waiting%20for%20Bisland%2C%20who%20never%20showed.%20%26quot%3BThe%20cause%20of%20this%20false%20information%20was%20never%20satisfactorily%20ascertained%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20later%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAfter%20the%20race%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Bly's%20train%20raced%20through%20the%20US%2C%20thousands%20of%20people%20gathered%20at%20different%20stops%20to%20cheer%20her%20on.%20On%20January%2025%2C%201890%2C%20she%20reached%20New%20Jersey%20after%2072%20days%2C%206%20hours%2C%2011%20minutes%2C%20and%2014%20seconds%20of%20travel.%20She%20had%20handily%20beat%20Verne's%20fictional%20Fogg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20storm-tossed%20voyage%20across%20the%20Atlantic%2C%20Bisland%20arrived%20home%20on%20January%2030%2C%20having%20completed%20a%2076-day%20journey%20around%20the%20globe.%20She%20was%20greeted%20with%20much%20less%20fanfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nellie%20bly%20sits%20in%20a%20chair%20in%20a%20puffy-sleeved%20dress%20with%20her%20hair%20up%20and%20a%20patterned%20blanket%20in%20the%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651e471542ecf94db4787307%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENellie%20Bly%20poses%20for%20a%20formal%20portrait.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20while%2C%20Bly%20was%20perhaps%20the%20most%20famous%20woman%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Goodman%20said.%20Companies%20started