%20human%20guide%20boats.%20In%20the%20summer%20of%202002%2C%20he%20traveled%201%2C000%20miles%20to%20the%20coast%20of%20Norway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeiko%20had%20many%20encounters%20with%20wild%20orcas%20but%20struggled%20to%20fully%20integrate%20with%20them.%20In%202003%2C%20five%20years%20after%20his%20release%2C%20Keiko%20died%20of%20pneumonia%20at%20the%20age%20of%2027.%20Wild%20male%20orcas%20typically%20live%20about%2035%20to%2050%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20Keiko%20wasn't%20able%20to%20integrate%20with%20wild%20orcas%2C%20critics%20of%20the%20effort%20describe%20his%20release%20as%20a%20failure.%20But%20animal%20rights%20activists%20say%20Keiko%20was%20able%20to%20regain%20his%20health%20after%20years%20in%20captivity%2C%20and%20while%20his%20death%20was%20premature%2C%20he%20had%20years%20of%20freedom%20in%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20plans%20were%20in%20place%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Flolita-orca-whale-leaving-miami-seaquarium-returning-home-2023-3%5C%22%3Erelease%20the%20captive%20orca%20Lolita%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20known%20as%20Tokitae%20or%20Toki%2C%20who%20had%20been%20at%20the%20Miami%20Seaquarium%20for%2050%20years.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Flolita-tokitae-orca-miami-seaquarium-died-captivity-before-returning-home-2023-8%5C%22%3Eshe%20died%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20complications%20of%20a%20suspected%20renal%20condition%20on%20August%2018%2C%202023%2C%20before%20she%20could%20be%20moved%20to%20a%20sea%20pen%20in%20her%20native%20waters%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Washington%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lolita%20or%20Tokitae%20the%20orca%20is%20shown%20jumpin%20out%20of%20the%20water%20in%20her%20small%20enclosure%20in%20the%20Miami%20Seaquarium.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ca277ace69770019841629%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22576%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20still%20from%20a%20video%20shows%20the%20Lolita%20or%20Tokitae%20the%20orca%20in%20the%20world's%20smallest%20orca%20enclosure.%3Cp%3EFile%20photo%2FMiami%20Herald%2FTribune%20News%20Service%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EWhale%20sanctuaries%20can%20help%20rehabilitate%20captive%20orcas%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKeiko's%20story%20is%20why%20orca%20experts%20and%20animal%20rights%20activists%20support%20the%20creation%20of%20whale%20sanctuaries%20or%20sea%20pens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20setting%2C%20orcas%20can%20swim%20free%20but%20remain%20close%20to%20humans%20who%20can%20help%20provide%20food%20and%20medical%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESanctuaries%20exist%20for%20other%20animals%20that%20have%20been%20released%20from%20captivity%2C%20like%20elephants%2C%20tigers%2C%20and%20bears.%20It's%20harder%20to%20establish%20these%20kinds%20of%20rehabilitation%20spaces%20for%20large%20ocean%20creatures%2C%20like%20killer%20whales%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhales-from-chinese-aquarium-starting-retirement-in-iceland-2019-6%5C%22%3Esea%20pen%20in%20Iceland%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20Keiko%20was%20released%20now%20houses%20two%20beluga%20whales%20and%20could%20potentially%20hold%20other%20marine%20mammals%2C%20including%20killer%20whales%2C%20Mark%20Palmer%2C%20associate%20director%20of%20the%20International%20Marine%20Mammal%20Project%2C%20told%20Insider.%20There%20are%20also%20several%20warm-water%20marine%20mammal%20sanctuaries%20being%20built%20in%20the%20Caribbean%20and%20Mediterranean%2C%20Palmer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Beluga%20Whales%20Little%20Grey%20and%20Little%20White%20swim%20in%20the%20bayside%20care%20pool%20before%20heading%20to%20Klettsvik%20Bay%20in%20Iceland.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6514b4a3eee46600193bb808%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20two%20beluga%20whales%2C%20Little%20Grey%20and%20Little%20White%2C%20before%20they%20were%20transferred%20to%20the%20same%20Iceland%20sanctuary%20where%20Keiko%20lived.%3Cp%3EAaron%20Chown%20-%20PA%20Images%20%2F%20Contributor%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELori%20Marino%2C%20founder%20and%20president%20of%20the%20Whale%20Sanctuary%20Project%2C%20is%20part%20of%20an%20effort%20to%20build%20the%20first-of-its-kind%20killer%20whale%20sanctuary%20in%20Nova%20Scotia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20completed%2C%20the%20sanctuary%20would%20occupy%20100%20acres%20of%20water%20space%20%E2%80%94%20big%20enough%20to%20fit%20about%2075%20standard%20American%20football%20fields.%20Depths%20in%20the%20sanctuary%20could%20reach%20up%20to%2059%20feet%2C%20which%20would%20allow%20orcas%20to%20swim%20farther%20and%20dive%20deeper%20than%20they%20can%20in%20marine%20park%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20SeaWorld%20orca%20tanks%20average%20approximately%2086%20feet%20by%2051%20feet%20with%20a%20depth%20of%2034%20feet%2C%20according%20to%20PETA.%20SeaWorld%20didn't%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20to%20confirm%20these%20measurements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20WSP%20is%20working%20to%20secure%20final%20funding%20with%20plans%20to%20complete%20the%20sanctuary%20in%202024%2C%20Palmer%20said.%20The%20sanctuary%20would%20also%20include%20underwater%20cameras%20and%20hydrophones%20for%20members%20of%20the%20public%20to%20learn%20about%20and%20observe%20the%20orcas%20from%20a%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20next%20step%20is%20to%20take%20these%2018%20remaining%20orcas%20in%20the%20US%20and%20bring%20them%20somewhere%20they%20can%20live%20out%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20lives%20in%20a%20more%20natural%2C%20healthy%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Marino%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20way%20to%20give%20back%20what%20was%20taken%20from%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20future%20of%20orca%20captivity%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMarino%20and%20other%20animal%20rights%20activists%20have%20urged%20SeaWorld%20to%20partner%20with%20them%20in%20efforts%20to%20build%20whale%20sanctuaries%2C%20but%20say%20so%20far%20the%20company%20has%20resisted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20unconscionable%20to%20risk%20the%20health%20and%20wellbeing%20of%20killer%20whales%20at%20SeaWorld%20by%20moving%20them%20to%20a%20sea%20pen%2C%20especially%20when%20killer%20whales%20at%20SeaWorld%20are%20living%20a%20healthy%20life%20in%20a%20safe%20and%20sound%20habitat%20where%20every%20need%20is%20attended%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20SeaWorld%20told%20Insider%20in%20an%20email%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Orcas%20in%20a%20tank%20at%20Seaworld's%20San%20Diego%20base.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6514b55feee46600193bb820%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22662%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECaptive%20orcas%20can't%20thrive%20in%20small%20tanks%20but%20may%20not%20thrive%20in%20the%20wild%2C%20either.%3Cp%3EPaul%20Harris%20%2F%20Contributor%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnimal%20rights%20activists%20say%20specifics%20about%20the%20health%20status%20of%20the%20orcas%20at%20SeaWorld%20are%20hard%20to%20come%20by%20as%20not%20much%20of%20that%20information%20is%20made%20public.%20But%20Dold%20said%20the%20orcas%20routinely%20undergo%20wellness%20checks%20that%20include%20taking%20blood%20samples%2C%20running%20diagnostic%20tests%2C%20and%20ultrasound%20imaging%20that%20show%20they're%20%26quot%3Bthriving%20under%20SeaWorld's%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDold%20also%20cited%20concerns%20about%20potential%20hurricanes%2C%20oil%20spills%2C%20infectious%20diseases%2C%20and%20disruption%20of%20the%20ocean%20ecosystem%20if%20the%20orcas%20at%20SeaWorld%20are%20moved%20to%20a%20sanctuary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarino%20said%20the%20WSP%20has%20worked%20to%20address%20these%20concerns%20in%20a%20few%20key%20ways%2C%20including%20a%20three-year%20environmental%20assessment%2C%20which%20found%20that%20allowing%20whales%20into%20the%20region%20would%20not%20harm%20the%20ecosystem.%20The%20WSP%20also%20chose%20the%20location%20in%20Nova%20Scotia%20specifically%20because%20of%20its%20protection%20from%20storm%20surges%20during%20hurricanes.%20And%20the%20team%20plans%20to%20include%20facilities%20for%20the%20whales%20to%20go%20to%20in%20the%20case%20of%20an%20oil%20spill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20disease%2C%20Marino%20explained%20the%20team%20would%20conduct%20a%20full%20workup%20of%20the%20orcas'%20health%20and%20immune%20systems%20before%20transferring%20them.%20The%20whales%20would%20also%20have%20access%20to%20veterinary%20care%20at%20the%20sanctuary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20to%20consider%20in%20this%20debate%20is%20what%20the%20public%20stands%20to%20lose%20if%20the%20orcas%20leave%20SeaWorld.%20The%20opportunity%20for%20people%20to%20see%20orcas%20up%20close%20and%20for%20scientists%20to%20study%20and%20learn%20about%20them%20has%20led%20to%20a%20greater%20appreciation%20of%20these%20animals%2C%20Dold%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222309%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Family%20of%20free%20orcas%20swimming%20together.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6514b5b41c099d0019ad54d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221299%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EScientists%20know%20more%20about%20orcas%20than%20we%20otherwise%20might%20because%20we've%20kept%20some%20in%20captivity%20for%20so%20long.%3Cp%3ESerge%20MELESAN%20%2F%20500px%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECaptive%20orcas%20have%20no%20doubt%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20expanding%20human%20knowledge%2C%20Shields%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20by%20studying%20captive%20orcas%2C%20scientists%20have%20been%20able%20to%20learn%20about%20orca%20gestation%20and%20metabolism%20%E2%80%94%20subjects%20that%20are%20much%20more%20difficult%20to%20research%20in%20free-ranging%20whales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Shields%20said%20this%20isn't%20a%20reason%20to%20continue%20keeping%20these%20animals%20in%20captivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20that%20increased%20understanding%20has%20also%20come%20increased%20respect%20and%20an%20awareness%20of%20just%20how%20much%20orcas%20suffer%20in%20a%20captive%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Shields%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20time%20to%20do%20right%20by%20these%20whales%20and%20give%20them%20the%20best%20retirement%20we%20can%20offer%20them%20and%20ultimately%20cease%20having%20orcas%20in%20captivity%20altogether.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaptive-orcas-seaworld-should-they-be-released-sea-pen-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696692541000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6514b2b51c099d0019ad548b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaptive-orcas-seaworld-should-they-be-released-sea-pen-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Captive%20orcas%20at%20SeaWorld%20can%20suffer%20severe%20health%20issues%2C%20but%20the%20solution%20isn't%20as%20simple%20as%20just%20releasing%20them%20into%20the%20wild.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Erin%20Heger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A56%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaptive-orcas-seaworld-should-they-be-released-sea-pen-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ireland%20vs%20Scotland%3A%20Rugby%20World%20Cup%20latest%20updates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696692360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F70x70%2Fskynews-england-worldcup_6312649.jpg%3F20231007163002%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fengland-vs-samoa-rugby-world-cup-latest-updates-12