s%20still%20owned%20a%20small%20plot%20of%20land%20in%20California%2C%20less%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20an%20acre%2C%20to%20grow%20food%20like%20collard%20greens%20and%20tomatoes%20and%20raise%20livestock%20to%20remain%20food%20secure.%20When%20Mason's%20mother%20died%2C%20her%20ashes%20were%20sprinkled%20among%20the%20collard%20patch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tradition%20of%20growing%20food%20is%20one%20that%20Mason%20has%20continued%2C%20maintaining%20a%20garden%20in%20every%20home%20she's%20lived%20in.%20Today%2C%20she's%20the%20president%20and%20cofounder%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jubileejustice.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJubilee%20Justice%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20cooperative%20of%20Black%20farmers%20and%20an%20organization%20that%20helps%20Black%20farming%20communities%20practice%20regenerative%20and%20sustainable%20agriculture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20always%20said%20when%20I%20grow%20up%2C%20I%20want%20to%20be%20a%20farmer.%20People%20thought%20I%20was%20kidding%20%E2%80%94%20I%20really%20wasn't%2C%26quot%3B%20Mason%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Konda%20Mason%20with%20rice%20businessman%20Robert%20Bimba%20and%20Jubilee%20Justice%20SRI%20advisor%20Erica%20Styger%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65203ced6561dd877e734161%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKonda%20Mason%20with%20rice%20businessman%20Robert%20Bimba%20and%20Jubilee%20Justice%20SRI%20advisor%20Erica%20Styger.%3Cp%3EKonda%20Mason%20courtesy%20of%20Jubilee%20Justice%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EReturning%20to%20the%20land%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20land%20was%20such%20a%20large%20part%20of%20Mason's%20family%20story%2C%20she%20said%20she%20didn't%20fully%20grasp%20how%20central%20it%20was%20to%20every%20conversation%20about%20race%20and%20money%20until%20later%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20Mason%20began%20a%20project%20called%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jubileejustice.org%2Fjubilee-journeys-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJubilee%20Journeys%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20series%20of%20conversations%20that%20bring%20together%20white%20participants%20who%20are%20financially%20well-off%20with%20spiritual%20and%20thought%20leaders%20from%20communities%20of%20color%20to%20promote%20racial%20healing%20and%20speak%20about%20the%20ways%20capital%20should%20be%20used%20and%20redistributed.%20She%20started%20these%20meetups%20hoping%20to%20talk%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhenry-blodget-better-capitalism-1-2018%5C%22%3Ealternatives%20to%20extractive%20capitalism%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20I%20realized%20it%20was%20about%20land%2C%26quot%3B%20Mason%20said.%20It%20sparked%20the%20four%20pillars%20that%20now%20guide%20her%20work%3A%20land%2C%20race%2C%20money%2C%20and%20spirit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20attendees%20to%20the%20first%20Journey%20in%20California%20was%20a%20woman%20named%20Elisabeth%20Keller.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20thing%20out%20of%20her%20mouth%20was%2C%20'I'm%20a%20white%20woman%20whose%20family%20owns%20a%20former%20plantation%20in%20Louisiana%2C'%26quot%3B%20Mason%20said.%20Keller's%20family%20had%20owned%20the%20roughly%203%2C000-acre%20Inglewood%20Farm%20property%20in%20Alexandria%20since%20her%20grandfather%20bought%20it%20in%20the%201920s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20wanted%20to%20kill%20what%20happened%20on%20this%20land%2C%20both%20to%20the%20land%2C%20which%20was%20very%20toxic%2C%20filled%20with%20chemicals%2C%26quot%3B%20Mason%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20what%20happened%20with%20the%20people%20here.%20It%20was%20a%20cotton%20plantation.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Civil%20War%2C%20formerly%20enslaved%20people%20and%20their%20descendants%20continued%20to%20work%20as%20sharecroppers%20on%20the%20plantation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMason%20suggested%20hosting%20the%20next%20Journeys%20conversation%20at%20Inglewood%20as%20a%20way%20to%20promote%20healing.%20The%20meeting%20was%20a%20success%2C%20leading%20to%20another%20the%20following%20year.%20At%20one%20of%20these%20discussions%2C%20an%20agricultural%20attorney%20talked%20openly%20about%20the%20plight%20of%20Black%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20so%20moved%20and%20it%20touched%20such%20a%20deep%20place%2C%20I%20just%20kept%20that%20in%20my%20heart%2C%26quot%3B%20Mason%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Donna%20Isaacs%2C%20a%20permaculture%20farmer%20and%20a%20member%20of%20Jubilee%20Justice%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65203ede6e038039826bf3aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDonna%20Isaacs%2C%20a%20permaculture%20farmer%20and%20a%20member%20of%20Jubilee%20Justice.%3Cp%3EDonna%20Isaacs%20courtesy%20of%20Jubilee%20Justice%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUp%20until%20this%20point%2C%20Mason%20had%20no%20background%20in%20farming.%20But%20three%20months%20later%2C%20at%20a%20conference%20in%20New%20York%2C%20Mason%20ran%20into%20Caryl%20Levine%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20the%20organic%20rice%20company%20Lotus%20Foods.%20She%20became%20fascinated%20with%20Levine's%20sustainable%20approach%20to%20rice%20farming.%20Levine%20had%20adopted%20an%20agriculture-management%20method%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fsri.ciifad.cornell.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESystem%20of%20Rice%20Intensification%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20uses%20up%20to%2050%25%20less%20water%2C%20requires%20up%20to%2090%25%20less%20seed%2C%20and%20can%20result%20in%2020%25%20to%20100%25%20more%20yield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrucially%2C%20this%20method%20also%20reduces%20methane%20emissions.%20Rice%20production%20is%20responsible%20for%2010%25%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fearth.org%2Fsystem-of-rice-intensification%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobal%20methane%20emissions%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20most%20of%20Lotus%20Foods'%20work%20was%20happening%20in%20Asia%20and%20Africa.%20Levine%20opened%20up%20about%20her%20desire%20to%20create%20a%20domestic%20supply%20chain%20of%20farmers%20in%20the%20US.%20Ideas%20began%20to%20converge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20said%20to%20her%2C%20'What%20about%20Black%20farmers%3F'%26quot%3B%20Mason%20said.%20Two%20weeks%20later%2C%20she%20was%20on%20a%20Zoom%20call%20making%20plans.%20The%20newly%20formed%20Jubilee%20Justice%20Rice%20Project%20would%20be%20centered%20on%20Inglewood%20Farm%2C%20what%20Mason%20describes%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20belly%20of%20the%20beast.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20where%20the%20worst%20of%20the%20worst%20has%20happened%2C%26quot%3B%20Mason%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20history%20of%20slavery%20on%20the%20plantation.%20%26quot%3BThe%20universe%20just%20really%20has%20this%20interesting%20way%20of%20bringing%20me%20here%20to%20this%20land.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELand%20loss%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERice%20isn't%20the%20only%20crop%20producing%20methane.%20In%202021%2C%20agriculture%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fghgemissions%2Fsources-greenhouse-gas-emissions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccounted%20for%2010%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20all%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20in%20the%20US.%20Modern-day%20farming%20practices%20release%20methane%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20from%20the%20soil%2C%20contributing%20to%20increased%20warming.%20Livestock%2C%20especially%20cows%2C%20produce%20methane%20as%20they%20digest%20grass%20and%20grains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENature%20is%20meant%20to%20be%20symbiotic.%20The%20insects%20and%20microbes%20that%20live%20in%20the%20soil%20capture%20carbon%20and%20convert%20it%20into%20organic%20material.%20But%20with%20the%20mass%20use%20of%20herbicides%20and%20pesticides%2C%20these%20beneficial%20organisms%20are%20killed%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20agrochemicals%20such%20as%20fertilizers%20began%20in%20the%201960s%20and%20resulted%20in%20dramatically%20higher%20crop%20yields%2C%20changing%20farming%20practices.%20Average%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ers.usda.gov%2Fwebdocs%2Fpublications%2F43854%2F46734_eib124.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecorn%20yield%20rose%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%2020%20bushels%20per%20acre%20in%201940%20to%20150%20bushels%20per%20acre%20by%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20partially%20due%20to%20pesticides%20and%20fertilizers.%20In%20that%20same%20period%20of%20time%2C%20cotton%20yields%20increased%20fourfold%20and%20soybean%20yields%20by%20threefold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20pests%20began%20to%20adapt%20to%20these%20chemicals%2C%20more%20agrochemicals%20continued%20to%20be%20introduced%2C%20leading%20to%20more%20environmental%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2020th%20century%20also%20changed%20the%20demographics%20of%20farmers%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201920%2C%20there%20were%20nearly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagcensus.library.cornell.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F1920-Farm_Statistics_By_Color_and_Tenure.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20Black%20farmers%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20accounting%20for%2014%25%20of%20all%20farmers.%20Today%2C%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nass.usda.gov%2FPublications%2FHighlights%2F2019%2F2017Census_Farm_Producers.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efewer%20than%2050%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20just%202%25%20of%20all%20farmers%20in%20the%20country%20are%20Black.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Jim%20Crow%20era%2C%20white%20landowners%20began%20intimidating%20Black%20farmers%20into%20abandoning%20their%20land.%20Violent%2C%20racist%20attacks%20led%20many%20Black%20farmers%20to%20flee%20the%20South%20as%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Great%20Migration.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government%20also%20practiced%20discrimination%20and%20intimidation%20tactics.%20A%201999%20class-action%20lawsuit%20against%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20claimed%20that%20the%20agency%20racially%20discriminated%20against%20Black%20farmers%20in%20distributing%20farm%20loans%2C%20forcing%20many%20of%20them%20into%20foreclosure.%20Per%20the%20settlement%20agreement%2C%20the%20USDA%20has%20paid%20or%20credited%20around%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-usa-farmers-pigford%2Fblack-farmers-win-1-25-billion-in-discrimination-suit-idUSTRE61H5XD20100218%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241%20billion%20to%20Black%20farmers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20it%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20civil-rights%20settlements%20in%20US%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20payout%2C%20however%2C%20was%20a%20drop%20in%20the%20ocean%20compared%20to%20the%20impact%20that%20land%20loss%20had%20on%20the%20racial%20wealth%20divide%20over%20the%20next%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201910%2C%20Black%20farmers%20owned%20between%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ers.usda.gov%2Fwebdocs%2Fpublications%2F46984%2F19353_ra174h_1_.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E16%20to%2019%20million%20acres%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20land%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Census%20of%20Agriculture.%20But%20between%201910%20and%201997%2C%20Black%20farmers%20lost%20around%2090%25%20of%20their%20property%2C%20while%20white%20farmers%20only%20lost%202%25%20during%20the%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aeaweb.org%2Farticles%3Fid%3D10.1257%2Fpandp.20221015%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20that%20land%20loss%20cost%20Black%20farmers%20around%20%24326%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20regenerative%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20Jubilee%20Justice%2C%20Mason%20wants%20to%20reclaim%20some%20of%20that%20history.%20She%20hopes%20to%20create%20a%20platform%20that%20addresses%20economic%20and%20racial%20equity%20for%20Black%20farmers%2C%20while%20also%20encouraging%20sustainable%20agriculture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20farmers%20who%20are%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Jubilee%20Justice%20network%20all%20emphasize%20regenerative%2C%20sustainable%2C%20organic%20forms%20of%20agriculture.%20Regenerative%20agriculture%20aims%20to%20work%20with%20nature%20rather%20than%20against%20it%20by%20rejuvenating%20soil%20health%2C%20boosting%20biodiversity%2C%20and%20developing%20practices%20that%20are%20climate%20resilient.%20Many%20of%20these%20farming%20practices%20were%20developed%20by%20Indigenous%20communities%20prior%20to%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20farmers%20in%20Jubilee%20Justice%20come%20from%20different%20backgrounds%20%E2%80%94%20some%20were%20raised%20on%20family%20farms%20while%20others%20built%20upon%20their%20interest%20in%20climate%20activism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Grand%20opening%20of%20the%20Jubilee%20Justice%20rice%20mill%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65203e116561dd877e734451%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221443%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGrand%20opening%20of%20the%20Jubilee%20Justice%20rice%20mill.%3Cp%3ELinda%20Jones%20courtesy%20of%20Jubilee%20Justice%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20they%20built%20a%20rice%20mill%20that%20they%20own%20as%20a%20cooperative.%20For%20Mason%2C%20being%20able%20to%20own%20the%20means%20of%20production%20is%20critical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20one%20of%20the%20ways%20that%20they%20kill%20Black%20farmers%20and%20take%20their%20land%20%E2%80%94%20they%20will%20have%20a%20contract%20and%20then%20next%20thing%20you%20know%20they%20reneg%20on%20that%20contract%2C%26quot%3B%20Mason%20said%20of%20relying%20too%20heavily%20on%20external%20vendors%20and%20manufacturers.%20%26quot%3BMost%20people%20are%20one%20season%20away%20from%20bankruptcy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJubilee%20Justice%20builds%20upon%20a%20legacy%20of%20Black%20farmer%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rd.usda.gov%2Ffiles%2FRR194.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecooperatives%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%2019th%20century%2C%20after%20the%20Southern%20Farmers'%20Alliance%20refused%20to%20admit%20Black%20farmers%20except%20in%20certain%20chapters%2C%20Black%20farmers%20started%20the%20Colored%20Farmers'%20National%20Alliance%20and%20Co-operative%20Union.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201891%2C%20they%20had%20over%20a%20million%20members.%20Following%20the%20civil-rights%20movement%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20there%20was%20a%20renewed%20interest%20in%20farming%20cooperatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20emphasizing%20cooperative%20economics%2C%20Mason%20hopes%20to%20move%20away%20from%20the%20mindset%20of%20hyper-individualism%20that%20capitalism%20values%20and%20to%20show%20Black%20farmers%20that%20if%20they%20rely%20on%20each%20other%2C%20the%20whole%20community%20can%20succeed%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20Mason%2C%20land%20is%20sacred.%20Mason%20reflected%20back%20to%20her%20years%20giving%20eco%20tours%20in%20the%20Ecuadorian%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20time%20I%20left%2C%20I%20would%20be%20in%20tears%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20want%20to%20go.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20leave%20it.%20I%20knew%20that%20it%20was%20in%20danger.%20It's%20such%20an%20impact%20to%20spend%20time%20in%20the%20rainforest%20and%20to%20understand%20this%20planet%20and%20how%20precious%20and%20beautiful%20it%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20just%20bent%20on%20leaving%20as%20much%20of%20a%20legacy%20as%20I%20possibly%20can%20and%20everything%20that%20I%20touch%20to%20come%20from%20a%20place%20of%20a%20regenerative%20mindset%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-farmers-jubilee-justice-louisiana-regenerative-farming-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696691942000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65203ede6e038039826bf3aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-farmers-jubilee-justice-louisiana-regenerative-farming-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20Black%20farmers%20in%20the%20US%20lost%2090%25%20of%20their%20land.%20New%20initiatives%20like%20Jubilee%20Justice%20hope%20to%20encourage%20economic%20equity%20and%20community.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tgopal%40insider.com%20(Trisha%20Gopal)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-farmers-jubilee-justice-louisiana-regenerative-farming-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Saudi%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman%20went%20from%20pariah%20to%20pragmatic%20diplomat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22MBS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65155cfa10de270019da5fbc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223043%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESaudi%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman.%3Cp%3EAFP%20Contributor%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESaudi%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman%20is%20trying%20to%20transform%20the%20oil-rich%20Persian%20Gulf%20kingdom.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20a%20rocky%20start%2C%20he's%20gained%20confidence%20on%20the%20world%20stage%20and%20launched%20bold%20diplomatic%20shifts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20reports%20of%20human-rights%20abuses%20in%20S