Fnews%2Fgst-council-cuts-tax-on-molasses-to-5-will-exempt-alcohol-from-levy-123100700423_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20GST%20Council%20on%20Saturday%20decided%20to%20reduce%20GST%20on%20molasses%20to%205%20per%20cent%2C%20from%2018%20per%20cent%2C%20and%20exempt%20alcohol%20for%20human%20consumption%20from%20the%20levy.%20Chhattisgarh%20Deputy%20Chief%20Minister%20T%20S%20Singh%20Deo%2C%20who%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20GST%20Council%2C%20said%20extra%20...%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fgst-council-cuts-tax-on-molasses-to-5-will-exempt-alcohol-from-levy-123100700423_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fgst-council-cuts-tax-on-molasses-to-5-will-exempt-alcohol-from-levy-123100700423_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fgst-council-cuts-tax-on-molasses-to-5-will-exempt-alcohol-from-levy-123100700423_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Corruption%20Shadow%20Over%20Candidate%20Shortlisted%20for%20Top%20Job%20in%20Railway%20Finance%20PSU%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F05%2F28145254%2F13286908034_bb8f865649_h.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Ministry%20of%20Railways%20is%20expected%20to%20conduct%20a%20set%20of%20interviews%20to%20fill%20the%20post%20of%20the%20chairman%20and%20the%20chief%20managing%20director%20(CMD)%20of%20its%20public%20sector%20unit%20(PSU)%2C%20the%20Indian%20Railway%20Finance%20Corporation%20(IRFC)%2C%20this%20Monday%2C%20on%20October%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20has%20been%20vacant%20for%20a%20year%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuestionable%20record%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20previous%20IRFC%20CMD%20and%20chairman%2C%20Amitabh%20Banerjee%2C%20was%20divested%20of%20his%20duties%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20immediate%20effect%E2%80%9D%20in%20October%202022.%20This%20happened%20after%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fthe-wire-impact-railways-finance-commission-amitabh-banerjee%5C%22%3Especial%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Railway%20Board%20and%20the%20Vigilance%20Directorate%20of%20the%20Railways%20had%20confirmed%20a%20full%20term%20for%20Banerjee%20in%20spite%20of%20a%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20FIR%20naming%20him%20in%20a%20multi-crore%20corruption%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt%20that%20the%20list%20of%20shortlisted%20candidates%20for%20the%20top%20post%20at%20IRFC%20to%20replace%20Banerjee%20includes%20an%20officer%2C%20Shelley%20Verma%2C%20who%20has%20held%20the%20post%20of%20the%20director%20(finance)%20at%20the%20PSU%20for%20some%20years%20now.%20She%20has%20also%20temporarily%20assumed%20the%20charge%20of%20the%20CMD.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVerma%2C%20however%2C%20is%20a%20controversial%20name%2C%20and%20her%20presence%20in%20the%20shortlist%20has%20raised%20both%2C%20eyebrows%20and%20questions.%20This%20is%20as%20she%2C%20in%20her%20capacity%20as%20director%20(finance)%2C%20had%20given%20monetary%20approval%2C%20on%20various%20occasions%20during%20her%20predecessor%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20tenure%2C%20to%20procure%20gold%20and%20silver%20medallions%20worth%20lakhs%20to%20allegedly%20gift%20%E2%80%98dignitaries%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESuch%20financial%20approvals%20were%20allegedly%20given%20by%20her%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20standing%20rules%20stating%20that%20PSUs%20are%20discouraged%20from%20giving%20expensive%20gifts%20to%20%E2%80%98dignitaries%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20no%20government%20official%20is%20allowed%20to%20accept%20any%20gifts%20during%20occasions%20such%20as%20Diwali%2C%20New%20Year%E2%80%99s%20Eve%2C%20Christmas%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOfficial%20gave%20approval%20to%20procure%20expensive%20%E2%80%98gifts%E2%80%99%20between%202020%20and%202021%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20government%20rules%20permit%20giving%20gifts%20only%20to%20promote%20commercial%20or%20business%20interests%2C%20a%20top%20railway%20official%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frailway-finance-commission-amitabh-banerjee-vigilance%5C%22%3Ehad%20told%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20October%202022%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20never%20been%20any%20need%20for%20the%20IRFC%20to%20bribe%20clients%20to%20give%20loans%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20lieu%20of%20an%20interest%20in%20private%20entities%20to%20build%20wagons%2C%20rolling%20stocks%2C%20etc.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20had%20spoken%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20case%20filed%20by%20the%20Railway%20vigilance%20department%20against%20then%20%E2%80%98IRFC%20employees%E2%80%99%2C%20including%20Banerjee%2C%20on%2030%20counts.%20These%20included%20allegations%20of%20financial%20misappropriation%20amounting%20to%20%E2%80%9C%2427%2C000%E2%80%9D%2C%20having%20spent%20as%20%E2%80%9Centertainment%20allowance%E2%80%9D%20to%20buy%20%E2%80%9Cexpensive%20watches%2C%20mobile%20phones%2C%20laptops%2C%20gold%20coins%2C%20expensive%20shawls%2C%20etc.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20exit%2C%20the%20Railway%20vigilance%20department%20noted%20the%20procurement%20of%20expensive%20gifts%20like%20gold%20and%20silver%20medallions%2C%20and%20pendants%2C%20from%20the%20Minerals%20and%20Metals%20Trading%20Corporation%20(MMTC)%2C%20during%20his%20term%2C%20prompting%20an%20inquiry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20official%20approvals%20to%20procure%20dozens%20of%20medallions%20(mementos)%20between%202020%20and%202021%20were%20allegedly%20given%20by%20Verma.%20These%20approvals%20under%20question%20have%20been%20perused%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETop%20IRFC%20officials%20fail%20to%20provide%20the%20list%20of%20beneficiaries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20vigilance%20inquiry%2C%20top%20IRFC%20officials%2C%20including%20Banerjee%2C%20failed%20to%20provide%20the%20list%20of%20%E2%80%98dignitaries%E2%80%99%20who%20were%20recipients%20of%20the%20gold%20and%20silver%20medallions%2C%20pendants%20and%20bars%2C%20costing%20lakhs%20of%20public%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt%20recently%20that%20two%20independent%20members%20of%20the%20Railway%20Board%20whom%20IRFC%20officials%20had%20claimed%20to%20have%20gifted%20gold%20medallions%20denied%20receiving%20any%2C%20thus%20putting%20the%20needle%20of%20suspicion%20on%20the%20top%20officials%2C%20including%20the%20then%20CMD.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20members%20denied%20receiving%20any%20such%20gifts%20during%20the%20vigilance%20probe.%20In%20addition%2C%20IRFC%20officials%20failed%20to%20provide%20the%20list%20of%20beneficiaries%2C%20and%20thereby%2C%20how%20the%20PSU%20benefitted%20from%20it.%20Therefore%2C%20%E2%80%9Cofficials%20of%20IRFC%20including%20Amitabh%20Banerjee%E2%80%9D%20came%20under%20the%20scanner%20for%20alleged%20embezzlement%20of%20public%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECBI%20files%20corruption%20case%20in%20August%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202023%2C%20the%20Vigilance%20Directorate%20of%20the%20Railways%20wrote%20to%20the%20CBI%20director%20to%20investigate%20the%20matter.%20On%20August%2028%2C%20the%20CBI%2C%20taking%20note%20of%20the%20request%20made%20by%20Bhaskar%20Roy%20Choudhury%2C%20joint%20director%20Vigilance%20(Intelligence)%20Railway%20Board%2C%20filed%20an%20FIR%20in%20Delhi%20under%20various%20sections%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20seen%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20CBI%20FIR%2C%20which%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5BThe%5D%20Vigilance%20Railway%20Board%20scrutinised%20two%20files%20of%20%5Bthe%5D%20IRFC%20and%20recorded%20statement%20and%20revealed%20serious%20irregularities%20with%20respect%20to%20procurement%20and%20distribution%20of%20gold%20and%20non-gold%20items.%20The%20extent%20of%20embezzlement%20is%20not%20provided%20in%20the%20complaint.%20The%20complaint%20alleged%20that%20private%20persons%20are%20also%20involved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20says%20%E2%80%9Csubstantive%20offences%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20stacked%20up%20against%20Banerjee%20and%20%E2%80%9Cother%20unknown%20public%20servants%20and%20unknown%20private%20persons%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShelly%20Verma%20is%20not%20named%20by%20the%20CBI%20in%20the%20August%2028%20case.%20The%20FIR%20has%20named%20only%20IRFC%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20Banerjee%20would%20have%20cleared%20the%20dubious%20purchases%2C%20which%20necessarily%20would%20have%20involved%20Verma%2C%20who%2C%20as%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20was%20director%20(finance)%20at%20the%20PSU.%20That%20is%20why%20her%20name%20among%20the%20shortlisted%20candidates%20is%20questionable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20too%2C%20while%20multiple%20instances%20of%20alleged%20corrupt%20practices%20and%20misuse%20of%20public%20money%20for%20personal%20gain%20was%20being%20investigated%20against%20him%2C%20the%20ministry%20and%20the%20Railway%20Board%20continued%20to%20keep%20him%20in%20the%20top%20post%20of%20the%20PSU%2C%20till%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frailway-finance-commission-amitabh-banerjee-vigilance%5C%22%3EExclusive%3A%20Rail%20Ministry%20Overlooked%20CBI%20FIR%20Against%20Key%20PSU%20Head%20Named%20for%20Causing%20Rs%20144%20Crore%20Loss%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETill%20then%2C%20as%20the%20PSU%E2%80%99s%20head%2C%20Banerjee%20was%20taking%20financial%20decisions%20on%20its%20behalf%20and%20had%20the%20right%20to%20seek%20foreign%20exchange%20from%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20green%20signal%20to%20Shelley%20Verma%E2%80%99s%20credentials%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20be%20able%20to%20hold%20the%20post%20of%20the%20CMD%20for%20a%20full%20term%2C%20the%20Vigilance%20Directorate%20of%20the%20Railways%20would%20also%20have%20to%20grant%20a%20green%20signal%20to%20Verma%E2%80%99s%20professional%20credentials%20and%20integrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20baffling%20is%2C%20while%20the%20railway%20vigilance%20department%20has%20found%20alleged%20embezzlement%20of%20funds%20due%20to%20an%20act%20in%20which%20Verma%20was%20closely%20involved%2C%20she%20has%20been%20allowed%20by%20the%20ministry%20and%20the%20Railway%20Board%2C%20thus%20far%2C%20to%20continue%20in%20the%20post%20of%20temporary%20CMD.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%205%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20emailed%20a%20set%20of%20queries%20to%20the%20Union%20minister%20of%20Railways%2C%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw%3B%20chairman%20and%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20the%20Railway%20Board%2C%20Jaya%20Verma%20Sinha%3B%20Anjali%20Goel%2C%20member%20(Finance)%20at%20the%20Railway%20Board%3B%20and%20Shobhana%20Bandopadhyay%2C%20principal%20executive%20director%20(vigilance)%20at%20the%20Railway%20Board%2C%20seeking%20answers%20to%20why%20an%20official%20under%20the%20scanner%20for%20alleged%20financial%20embezzlement%20has%20been%20shortlisted%20for%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20questions%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20asked%20whether%20she%20has%20been%20granted%20vigilance%20clearance%20to%20hold%20the%20post%2C%20and%20also%20why%20she%20was%20appointed%20to%20temporarily%20take%20charge%20of%20the%20CMD%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20even%20after%20the%20CBI%20had%20filed%20a%20corruption%20case%20on%20the%20matter%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20story%20will%20be%20updated%20as%20and%20when%20they%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696678243000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F05%2F28145254%2F13286908034_bb8f865649_h.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcorruption-shadow-over-candidate-shortlisted-for-top-job-in-railway-finance-psu%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20railway%20vigilance%20department%20has%20found%20alleged%20embezzlement%20of%20public%20funds%20due%20to%20an%20act%20in%20which%20Shelly%20Verma%20was%20also%20allegedly%20involved.%20But%20she%20has%20been%20allowed%20by%20the%20authorities%2C%20thus%20far%2C%20to%20continue%20in%20the%20post%20of%20temporary%20CMD.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcorruption-shadow-over-candidate-shortlisted-for-top-job-in-railway-finance-psu%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20Rarely%20Do%20Those%20in%20Power%20Admit%20They%20Were%20Wrong%20%E2%80%93%20That's%20What%20Makes%20Emperor%20Ashoka%20Unique%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07161408%2Fashoka-collage.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20new%20book%20%3Cem%3EAshoka%3A%20Portrait%20of%20a%20Philosopher%20King%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Professor%20Patrick%20Olivelle%20talks%20about%20the%20life%2C%20moral%20philosophy%20and%20ideals%20of%20Mauryan%20emperor%20Ashoka.%20The%20book%20is%20the%20first%20in%20a%20new%20series%20edited%20by%20Ramachandra%20Guha%2C%20%E2%80%98Indian%20Lives%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20uses%20biographies%20to%20tell%20the%20story%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOlivelle%20and%20Guha%20sat%20down%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20talk%20about%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20the%20characteristics%20that%20set%20him%20apart%20