D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F11144004%2Fcure-1006824_960_720.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20affiliate%20Laghu%20Udyog%20Bharati%20(LUB)%20has%20urged%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20adopt%20a%20more%20considerate%20approach%20when%20inspecting%20micro%20and%20small%20pharmaceutical%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELUB%20has%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20potential%20medicine%20shortages%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20due%20to%20an%20atmosphere%20of%20%E2%80%9Capprehension%E2%80%9D%20caused%20by%20ongoing%20inspections%20and%20notifications%20of%20closures%20or%20production%20halts%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news18.com%2Findia%2Finspections-resembling-raids-rss-affiliate-urges-centre-to-overlook-minor-lapses-in-pharma-firms-8606652.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENews18%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20body%20is%20a%20registered%20national-level%20organisation%2C%20working%20for%20the%20cause%20of%20micro%2C%20small%20and%20medium%20enterprises%20in%20over%20400%20districts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20letter%20from%20LUB%20on%20this%20issue.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news18.com%2Findia%2Finspections-brought-bad-name-to-indian-drugmakers-rss-affiliated-msme-lobby-writes-to-health-ministry-8261557.html%5C%22%3Eprevious%20one%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sent%20in%20July%2C%20was%20retracted%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20sent%20due%20to%20some%20%E2%80%9Cconfusion%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20latest%20letter%20titled%20%E2%80%98Urgent%20Action%20Required%20to%20Preserve%20the%20MSME%20Pharma%20Industry%2C%E2%80%99%20LUB%20has%20requested%20the%20government%20to%20avoid%20%E2%80%9Cminor%20lapses%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20letter%20was%20sent%20to%20Union%20health%20minister%20Mansukh%20Mandaviya%20on%20October%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20argues%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cminimum%20three-year%20period%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20industry%20to%20adapt%20to%20Schedule%20M%2C%20calling%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20deadline%20of%20six%20months%20to%20one%20year%20%E2%80%9Cimpractical%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20and%20Family%20Welfare%2C%20through%20its%20drug%20regulatory%20arm%2C%20the%20Central%20Drugs%20Standard%20Control%20Organisation%20(CDSCO)%2C%20has%20been%20conducting%20risk-based%20inspections%20at%20select%20companies%20following%20concerns%20raised%20by%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20and%20several%20other%20countries%20regarding%20the%20quality%20of%20Indian%20medicines.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Inspections%20resembling%20raids%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%2C%20also%20marked%20to%20the%20health%20secretary%20and%20Drug%20Controller%20General%20of%20India%2C%20emphasises%20%E2%80%9Cpatient%20safety%20and%20health%20over%20minor%20documentation%20discrepancies%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20we%20wholeheartedly%20support%20risk-based%20inspections%20initiative%2C%20we%20have%20observed%20that%2C%20in%20the%20last%2030%20days%2C%20several%20MSME%20units%20were%20inspected%20in%20a%20manner%20resembling%20a%20raid%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ghan%20Shyam%20Ojha%2C%20all-India%20president%20of%20LBU%2C%20wrote%20in%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOjha%2C%20in%20the%20letter%20accessed%20by%20%3Cem%3ENews18%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20advocate%20for%20a%20more%20considered%20approach%20to%20inspections%2C%20especially%20for%20small%20shortfalls%20(sic)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20inspections%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20shut%20down%20the%20units%20and%20production%20lines%20when%20not%20found%20complying%20with%20good%20manufacturing%20practices.%20However%2C%20LBU%20demands%20a%20change%20in%20its%20stance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConcluding%20the%20letter%2C%20LBU%20warned%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6shortages%20of%20medicines%20may%20be%20observed%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20which%20poses%20a%20threat%20to%20humanity%2C%20as%20our%20manufacturers%20are%20in%20deep%20dilemma%20and%20it%20has%20created%20fear%20factor%20among%20all%20of%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20requested%20an%20appointment%20with%20the%20minister%20to%20discuss%20the%20issue%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20confirming%20the%20dispatch%20of%20the%20four-page-long%20letter%2C%20Ojha%20told%20%3Cem%3ENews18%3C%2Fem%3E%20over%20a%20call%20that%20LBU%20is%20awaiting%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20response.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20expect%20a%20favourable%20response%20considering%20the%20future%20of%20the%20Indian%20pharma%20industry%20which%20has%20flourished%20on%20its%20strong%20foundation%20of%20MSME.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Upgrading%208%2C000%20units%20to%20Schedule%20M%20within%20one%20year%20is%20impractical%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20the%20health%20ministry%20announced%20that%20pharmaceutical%20companies%20with%20an%20annual%20turnover%20exceeding%20Rs%20250%20crore%20must%20adhere%20to%20Schedule%20M%20standards%2C%20which%20are%20equivalent%20to%20WHO-GMP%20certification%2C%20within%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECompanies%20with%20a%20turnover%20less%20than%20Rs%20250%20crore%20were%20given%20one%20year%20to%20comply.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20LUB%20has%20emphasised%20in%20the%20letter%20that%20the%20industry%20requires%20a%20minimum%20of%20three%20years%20to%20implement%20these%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20argues%20that%20the%202018%20draft%20rule%20should%20not%20be%20enforced%20hastily%2C%20as%20it%20took%2077%20years%20to%20reach%20this%20point%2C%20and%20upgrading%208%2C000%20units%20to%20Schedule%20M%20within%20one%20year%20is%20impractical.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20points%20out%20that%20the%20pharmaceutical%20industry%20is%20already%20subject%20to%20numerous%20regulations%2C%20including%20those%20related%20to%20narcotics%2C%20labour%2C%20pollution%20(both%20at%20the%20central%20and%20state%20levels)%2C%20and%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELUB%20asserts%20that%20if%20each%20regulatory%20body%20were%20to%20initiate%20risk-based%20inspections%2C%20it%20would%20be%20unmanageable%20for%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Adopt%20a%20holistic%20approach%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELUB%20cited%20an%20example%20of%20a%20US-based%20pharmaceutical%20company%2C%20Abbott%20(without%20explicitly%20naming%20it)%2C%20to%20illustrate%20that%20even%20large%20corporates%20with%20top-tier%20approvals%20frequently%20fail%20to%20meet%20quality%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELUB%20highlighted%20that%20companies%20with%20USFDA%2C%20EU-GMP%2C%20and%20WHO-GMP%20certifications%20have%20experienced%20quality%20lapses%2C%20resulting%20in%20recalls%20of%20their%20products%20in%20both%20global%20and%20Indian%20markets.%20LUB%20has%20called%20upon%20the%20government%20to%20adopt%20a%20holistic%20approach%20in%20addressing%20the%20issue%20of%20%E2%80%9CNot%20of%20Standard%20Quality%20(NSQ)%E2%80%9D%20rather%20than%20exclusively%20targeting%20the%20pharmaceutical%20formulation%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20argue%20that%20NSQ%20determinations%20are%20influenced%20by%20various%20factors%2C%20including%20transportation%20issues%2C%20quality%20assessments%2C%20laboratory%20efficiency%2C%20storage%20conditions%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696673197000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F11144004%2Fcure-1006824_960_720.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Finspections-resembling-raids-rss-affiliate-urges-govt-to-avoid-minor-lapses-in-pharma-firms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Laghu%20Udyog%20Bharati%20has%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20potential%20medicine%20shortages%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20due%20to%20an%20atmosphere%20of%20%26quot%3Bapprehension%26quot%3B%20caused%20by%20ongoing%20inspections%20and%20notifications%20of%20closures%20or%20production%20halts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Finspections-resembling-raids-rss-affiliate-urges-govt-to-avoid-minor-lapses-in-pharma-firms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98The%20Liver%20Doc%E2%80%99%20Abby%20Philips%20Moves%20High%20Court%20To%20Get%20X%20Account%20Restored%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07150301%2FScreenshot-2023-10-07-at-3.02.03%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Hepatologist%20Dr%20Cyraic%20Abby%20Philips%20has%20moved%20the%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20against%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20and%20Himalaya%20Wellness%20Corporation%20for%20the%20restoration%20of%20his%20popular%20account%20%40theliverdr%20or%20%E2%80%98The%20Liver%20Doc%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20confirmed%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20a%20petition%20had%20been%20filed%2C%20without%20going%20into%20any%20further%20details.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fdr-cyriac-abby-philips-x-account-suspensi-239549%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20petition%20was%20filed%20on%20Friday%20and%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20mentioned%20before%20a%20single-judge%20bench%20of%20Justice%20S.G.%20Pandit%20on%20Monday%20for%20an%20early%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EX%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fx-account-of-the-liver-doc-suspended-after-court-issues-ex-parte-injunction-in-suit-filed-by-himalaya%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewithheld%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20his%20account%20in%20India%20on%20September%2028%20after%20a%20Bengaluru%20civil%20court%20passed%20an%20ex-parte%2C%20interim%20injunction%20order%20against%20him%20in%20a%20case%20filed%20by%20Himalaya%2C%20which%20had%20claimed%20the%20doctor%20made%20defamatory%20statements%20against%20company%20products%20like%20Liv-52.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBefore%20his%20X%20account%20was%20suspended%2C%C2%A0Philips%20countered%20practices%20in%20alternate%20medicine%20systems%20like%20Ayurveda%2C%20Unani%2C%20Siddha%20and%20Homeopathy%20that%20he%20said%20caused%20liver%20damage%20in%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETalking%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20at%20that%20time%2C%20Philips%20said%20that%20since%20it%20was%20an%20ex-parte%20injunction%2C%20he%20did%20not%20get%20the%20chance%20to%20make%20his%20defence%2C%20adding%20that%20his%20posts%20were%20evidence-based%20and%20were%20available%20for%20public%20review.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhilips%20has%20garnered%20a%20lot%20of%20support%20from%20doctors%2C%20patients%20and%20many%20others%20on%20social%20media%20after%20his%20account%20was%20suspended.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsathicehat.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2FALLIAN1.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAlliance%20of%20Doctors%20for%20Ethical%20Healthcare%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(ADEH)%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20pan-India%20network%20of%20doctors%2C%20issued%20a%20press%20statement%20on%20October%203%20in%20his%20support.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20organisation%20of%20doctors%20to%20do%20so.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20that%20this%20doctor%2C%20among%20others%2C%20have%20been%20rendering%20yeoman%20service%20to%20the%20people%20of%20India%20by%20identifying%20non-scientific%20methodologies%20of%20the%20purported%20cures%3B%20and%20exposing%20harmful%20effects%20of%20some%20of%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ADEH%20also%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20doctor%20was%20not%20served%20any%20legal%20notice%20and%20to%20suspend%20his%20account%20in%20such%20an%20arbitrary%20fashion%20is%20unusual.%20We%20are%20puzzled%20as%20to%20what%20constitutes%20urgency%20in%20this%20case%2C%20for%20the%20court%20to%20take%20such%20a%20step.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHimalaya%20had%20alleged%20that%20Philips%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Cposting%20derogatory%20statements%20against%20the%20products%20of%20the%20company%20due%20to%20which%20it%20has%20lost%20substantial%20business%E2%80%9D.%20It%20had%20also%20accused%20Philips%20of%20working%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20companies%20like%20Cipla%20and%20Alchem%20%E2%80%93%20an%20allegation%20that%20Philips%20said%20was%20preposterous.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CRather%20it%E2%80%99s%20me%20who%20finds%20the%20order%20defamatory.%20Himalaya%20has%20alleged%20I%20was%20writing%20Twitter%20posts%20%5Bdebunking%20myths%20of%20certain%20ayurveda%20products%5D%20on%20behalf%20of%20certain%20companies%20and%20to%20promote%20their%20products%E2%80%A6But%20Himalaya%20failed%20to%20give%20any%20evidence%20to%20prove%20this%20claim%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20had%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20defamation%20suit%20filed%20by%20Himalaya%20has%20sought%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fscienceisdope_%2Fstatus%2F1708822786838565021%3Fs%3D48%26t%3D1vwSP919utJCl83SiqVxmg%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERs%2010%20crore%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(Rs%201.2%20million)%20in%20damages%20from%20him.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnother%20company%2C%20another%20notice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20another%20incident%2C%20a%20Chennai-based%20ayurveda%20firm%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.kesarikuteeram.in%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKesari%20Kuteeram%20Private%20Limited%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20has%20sent%20a%20legal%20notice%20to%20him.%20Philips%20posted%20about%20the%20death%20of%20a%20pregnant%20woman%20after%20she%20consumed%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20herbal%20product%20Madhiphala%20Rasayanam%20because%20of%20%E2%80%9Csevere%20herbal%20liver%20injury%E2%80%9D.%20His%20lab%20would%20review%20and%20analyse%20the%20product%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20Dr%20Philips%20did%20not%20accuse%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20product%20of%20causing%20the%20death%2C%20only%20that%20he%20was%20asked%20to%20analyse%20and%20review%20its%20composition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07145849%2FScreenshot-2023-10-07-at-2.05.17%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221044%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07145849%2FScreenshot-2023-10-07-at-2.05.17%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201044w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07145849%2FScreenshot-2023-10-07-at-2.05.17%25E2%2580%25AFPM-261x300.png%20261w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07145849%2FScreenshot-2023-10-07-at-2.05.17%25E2%2580%25AFPM-891x1024.png%20891w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678825%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Screengrab%20via%20X%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKesari%20Kuteeram%20said%20in%20the%20notice%20that%20his%20conclusion%20was%20based%20on%20%E2%80%98hearsay%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98wholly%20incorrect%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98defamatory%E2%80%99%20against%20the%20company.%20It%20also%20said%20the%20%E2%80%98goodwill%20of%20the%20client%E2%80%99%20has%20been%20%E2%80%98degraded%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%20It%20also%20accused%20Philips%20of%20having%20a%20bias%20against%20the%20%E2%80%